  "prompt": "How does moon shine?",
  "response": "The Moon shines due to the reflection of sunlight. It does not generate its own light, but rather reflects the light from the Sun. The surface of the Moon is covered with dust and rocky material that reflects sunlight. When the Sun's light hits the Moon, it bounces off and travels to Earth, making the Moon appear bright in the night sky. The amount of Moon that is illuminated and visible from Earth changes as the Moon orbits the Earth, leading to the different phases of the Moon.",
